      • create

        public BatchResponse create(BatchRequest batchRequest,
                            java.lang.Boolean atomic)
        Description copied from interface: Batch
        Enables you to make multiple API requests using a single request. The batch API takes in an array of logical HTTP requests represented as JSON arrays. Each request has a method (GET, PUT, POST, or DELETE), a relative_url (the portion of the URL after https:///api/), optional headers array (corresponding to HTTP headers) and an optional body (for POST and PUT requests). The batch API returns an array of logical HTTP responses represented as JSON arrays. Each response has a status code, an optional headers array and an optional body (which is a JSON-encoded string).

        Synchronous method overload. Result of the invocation will be reported as a method return value.
